        <ul><b>NDS Process Flow</b>
            <li>Call or email us regarding scheduling a time to perform a site visit</li>
            <li>Receive & review NDS Scope of work/ agreement</li> 
            <li>Sign the NDS agreement & pay invoice (all major Credit cards accepted)</li>
            <li>Schedule service date</li>
            <li>5 Step treatment service preformed</li>
            <li>Receive the “Certificate of Disinfection”</li>
        </ul>
        <ul><b>NDS Treatment Process</b>
        <li>Our multi-man team, including an area Manager or Supervisor will arrive at your location.</li>

        <li>Step 1 - We do an advanced ATP (Adenosine triphosphate) test, using Ensuretouch by Hygenia, this is a 
        effective method that’s used to quickly determined the sanitation of various high touch surfaces. ATP is 
        an indicator of biological residue that can be easily detected to measure cleanliness because effective 
        because cleaning and sanitization removes all ATP from surfaces enabling rapid detection of microbial residue.</li>

        <li>Step 2 - Introduce a Negative air machine with Hepa Filter used in Hospitals to purify air to eradicate 
            aerosolized particles down to 3 microns. </li>
        <li>Step 3 - Ultra Low Volume (ULV) fogging machine/ Electrostatic Spray application of EPA registered and CDC 
            approved Hospital Grade disinfectant. Positively Charged ions are produced within chemical which adhere to 
            surfaces in treated areas. This ensures total coverage of the treated area for wiping and disruption of Biofilm.</li>
        <li>Step 4 - After a 12-minute dwell time surface wiping of High touch areas begin. Fixtures , Keyboards, phones, 
            door handles, and other critical contact areas are hand wiped.</li>  
        <li>Step 5 - We will perform a post disinfection ATP test to measure elimination of pathogens.</li>
        </ul>
